Preparation of 4-(4-cyclobutylpiperazin-1-yl)benzoic acid (64)


(i) Methyl 4-(piperazin-1-yl)benzoate (CAS 163210-97-7, 500 mg, 2.27 mmol) was dissolved in THF (10 mL) and water (0.2 mL) with stirring. Cyclobutanone (0.238 g, 3.4 mmol) was added followed by acetic acid (0.5 mL) and sodium cyanoborohydride (0.211 g, 3.4 mmol). The mixture was refluxed for 6 h, cooled and reduced in vacuo. The residue was dissolved in 1N HCl (3 mL) and water (12 mL) then washed with ethyl acetate (2×10 mL). The aqueous layer was adjusted to pH 10 with potassium carbonate and extracted with ethyl acetate (3×10 mL). The combined organics were dried (MgSO
4
), filtered and reduced in vacuo to give crude methyl ester (0.56 g).


(ii) Methyl ester (0.51 g, assume 1.85 mmol) was suspended in 10% NaOH (3 mL) and water (3 mL) added. The mixture was heated at 80° C. for 2 h; then cooled to 0° C. The mixture was acidified to pH 2 with 6N HCl, then cooled for 2 h at −5° C. A tan solid was filtered and washed thoroughly with hexane and dried in vacuo to give acid (64) (yield 0.25 g). HPLC-MS 261 [M+H]
+
.


