Preparation of 4(1-cyclobutylpiperidin-4-yl)benzoic acid (67)


(i) Methyl 4-(piperidin-4-yl)benzoate (CAS 281235-04-9, 0.25 g, 1.13 mmol) was dissolved in a mixture of THF (6 mL) and water (0.1 mL). Acetic acid (0.25 mL) and cyclobutanone (0.119 g, 1.7 mmol) were added followed by sodium cyanoborohydride (0.15 g, 2.4 mmol). The mixture was refluxed for 5 h then cooled and reduced in vacuo. The residue was dissolved in 1N HCl (4 mL) and water (15 mL) then washed with ethyl acetate (2×10 mL). The aqueous layer was adjusted to pH 10 with potassium carbonate and extracted with ethyl acetate (3×10 mL). The combined organics were washed with brine then dried (MgSO
4
), filtered and reduced in vacuo to give crude methyl ester (0.23 g).


